snippet.textDisplay:
What I want to know is what will they name the "50" series when it releases.
The 1660 is just so random it allows for no sensible follow-ups following the same naming scheme.j
1650 is obviously awful as it makes the 6 completely arbitrary and useless.
1550 is also horrible as it's just having the '5' in twice for no good reason. And it ignores their silly "closer to 20 than 10" argument for the 1660.


Plus what about the next generation? The high-end will probably be 30x0, but what about the lower end? Will we have a 2160? A 2660? Both are far worse than the 1660.
In choosing an awful name they've dug a massive hole, setting themselves up for a bunch more even worse names.

snippet.textDisplay:
Are people actually concerned about their "privacy" in a COMMERCIAL AIRLINER? Or, are they just bothered about actually seeing these cameras, unlike the rest of the cameras spread across society that we all just conveniently ignore every day?
There really isn't a controversy here; you're in a PUBLIC space when you're on an airliner, you don't get to selectively be outraged when it's convenient.

And, yes, anyone with a functioning brain should've realized that watching shows on the internet behind a pay wall isn't any different than watching them on cable behind a pay wall - unless you don't watch a variety of shows/events, you're going to have to pay for multiple services(...or 'packages', if you will...), and it's likely going to add up to the cost of the average cable bill. 
And ALL of the services that possess the rights to top programming will be or are already owned by the handful of global media conglomerations, like Disney.
"Surprise surprise"
